					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One compromise between the tile animation capability of CHR ROM and the other flexibility of CHR RAM is a 32 KiB CHR RAM. Yes, this can be expressed in NES 2.0, and a 62256 shouldn't be that much more expensive than a 6264.
<br />
<br />Do you plan to allow for both standard and TLSROM-style nametable mirroring?
<br />
<br />Or a switchable fixed bank for multicart use?
<br />
<br />For replication in quantity, how much would it save to leave off the USB access or use a smaller PRG flash?</div>

